{"id":14881484,"mediaExerciseId":"755cc5e6-2eff-4bbb-a134-39823803390f","exerciseName":"1","chapterName":"14","chapterTitle":"Cost of Capital","groupId":612389,"groupTitle":"Excel Master IT! Problem","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":494,"solutions":[{"id":6440524,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will visit a website that can be used in order to access available information on publicly traded stocks in the market. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"When investing in stocks, traders can only use publicly available information of the companies that they are trading. Among these information are the book value of the debt and the book value of the equity.\n\nThere are two important values that we need to remember: book value and market value. The book value simply refers to the value of the equity or the debt that the company declares in their books. On the other hand, the market value is the value of the company's debt and equity as valued by the market. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"For this company, we can look at the book value of their equity and the book value of their debt by visiting the website indicated in the book.\n\nOnce there, we can see that the values are:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Book value of equity}&=\\$315,830,000,000\\\\[15 pt]\n\\text{Book value of debt}&=\\$88,730,000,000\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"3044ecfd-0b71-4d8c-b9d8-15069b0386a1","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Step